      <h2>Why Commercial Battery Storage?</h2>
      <p>
        For many businesses, the highest cost on the electricity bill isn't total consumption — it's <strong>peak demand charges</strong>. These charges are based on the highest power draw recorded during a billing period, even if it only lasts 15–30 minutes.
      </p>
      <p>
        A battery system reduces peak demand by discharging stored energy during high-draw periods, keeping your maximum grid draw below the threshold. This is called <strong>peak shaving</strong>, and it can deliver significant savings — especially for businesses with variable loads.
      </p>

      <h2>How It Works</h2>
      <p>
        The battery charges from your solar system during the day (or from the grid during off-peak hours). When your building's energy demand spikes, the battery discharges to supplement grid power, keeping the total grid draw below a set limit.
      </p>
      <p>
        The system is managed by intelligent controls that monitor your load in real time and respond automatically — no manual intervention required.
      </p>

      <h2>Key Benefits</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Peak demand reduction</strong> — lower the demand charges that make up a significant portion of commercial electricity bills</li>
        <li><strong>Solar self-consumption</strong> — store excess solar generation instead of exporting it at low feed-in rates</li>
        <li><strong>Backup power</strong> — maintain operations during grid outages for critical loads</li>
        <li><strong>Energy arbitrage</strong> — charge during cheap off-peak periods, discharge during expensive peak periods</li>
        <li><strong>Future-proofing</strong> — as grid costs rise and tariff structures change, battery flexibility becomes more valuable</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Behind-the-Meter Installation</h2>
      <p>
        Our commercial batteries are installed behind the meter — meaning they sit between the grid connection and your building's switchboard. The system is invisible to the grid operator and doesn't require complex export agreements.
      </p>

      <h2>Paired With Solar</h2>
      <p>
        Battery storage delivers the best return when paired with an appropriately sized <a href="/services/commercial/solar-systems">commercial solar system</a>. Solar provides free daytime energy to charge the battery, and the battery extends those savings into evening and peak periods.
      </p>

      <p>
        <a href="/services/consultation">Book a free consultation</a> to assess battery storage for your business.
      </p>
    </div>
